content:
Creating a full-fledged e-commerce website involves a considerable amount of code, but I can provide you with a basic structure to get you started. This will include HTML, CSS, and some JavaScript for the interactive elements.

### HTML

#### index.html (Homepage)

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Shoe E-commerce</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Shoe Store</h1>
        <input type="text" placeholder="Search for shoes..." id="search-bar">
    </header>
    <nav>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="#">Men</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Women</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Kids</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>
    <main>
        <section id="new-arrivals">
            <h2>New Arrivals</h2>
            <div class="shoe-card">...</div> <!-- Repeat for each shoe -->
        </section>
    </main>
    <footer>
        <p>© 2023 Shoe Store</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

#### product.html (Product Page)

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Product Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Shoe Store</h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <section id="product-details">
            <h2>Product Name</h2>
            <div class="gallery">
                <img src="shoe1.jpg" alt="Shoe Image 1" class="active">
                <img src="shoe2.jpg" alt="Shoe Image 2">
            </div>
            <p>Price: $100</p>
            <button>Add to Cart</button>
        </section>
    </main>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

### CSS (styles.css)

```css
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

header {
    background-color: #333;
    color: white;
    padding: 10px;
    text-align: center;
}

nav ul {
    list-style-type: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    background-color: #444;
}

nav ul li {
    margin: 0 15px;
}

nav ul li a {
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
}

#new-arrivals {
    padding: 20px;
}

.shoe-card {
    border: 1px solid #ccc;
    padding: 10px;
    margin: 10px;
    text-align: center;
}

.gallery {
    display: flex;
}

.gallery img {
    width: 100px;
    height: auto;
    margin-right: 10px;
    cursor: pointer;
}

.gallery img.active {
    border: 2px solid blue;
}

footer {
    background-color: #333;
    color: white;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 10px;
    position: fixed;
    width: 100%;
    bottom: 0;
}
```

### JavaScript (script.js)

```javascript
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const images = document.querySelectorAll('.gallery img');
    images.forEach(image => {
        image.addEventListener('click', () => {
            images.forEach(img => img.classList.remove('active'));
            image.classList.add('active');
        });
    });
});
```

### Explanation

- **Homepage**: Includes a header with a search bar, navigation for shoe categories, and a section for new arrivals.
- **Product Page**: Displays product details and includes a simple gallery that switches the active image when clicked.
- **CSS**: Basic styling for the layout and interactive elements.
- **JavaScript**: Simple script to handle the image gallery interactivity.

This is a foundational setup. For a full-fledged e-commerce site, you would typically use a backend framework, integrate a database, and implement secure payment processing, among other features.
